WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.675 align:middle line:90%
[ Music & Noise ]

00:00:20.187 --> 00:00:22.689 align:middle line:84%
>> For those of you who are
seeking a deeper understanding

00:00:22.689 --> 00:00:25.525 align:middle line:84%
of the fabric of reality,
including their own lives,

00:00:25.525 --> 00:00:28.261 align:middle line:84%
Ayahuasca has been
a facilitator.

00:00:28.261 --> 00:00:29.997 align:middle line:84%
As with a number
of my interviewees,

00:00:29.997 --> 00:00:32.866 align:middle line:84%
Author Graham Hancock has
placed his Ayahuasca journeys

00:00:32.866 --> 00:00:34.901 align:middle line:84%
as among the most sacred
events of his life.

00:00:34.901 --> 00:00:38.405 align:middle line:84%
He believes that with the
help of mind expanding agents,

00:00:38.405 --> 00:00:41.074 align:middle line:84%
we will better be able to
piece together the deep history

00:00:41.074 --> 00:00:42.609 align:middle line:90%
of the human experience,

00:00:42.609 --> 00:00:44.711 align:middle line:84%
where archeological
evidence leaves off,

00:00:44.711 --> 00:00:47.047 align:middle line:84%
our collective memory
can fill in the gaps.

00:00:47.047 --> 00:00:48.448 align:middle line:90%
I met with Graham in Scottsdale,

00:00:48.448 --> 00:00:51.051 align:middle line:84%
Arizona at the Earth-Keeper's
Conference to speak

00:00:51.051 --> 00:00:55.689 align:middle line:84%
about Ayahuasca and the right to
sovereignty over our own minds.

00:00:55.689 --> 00:00:58.025 align:middle line:90%
It's good to see you again.

00:00:58.025 --> 00:00:59.292 align:middle line:90%
It's been a couple of years.

00:00:59.292 --> 00:01:01.728 align:middle line:84%
Last time we sat together,
you had just finished--

00:01:01.728 --> 00:01:04.064 align:middle line:84%
I think you only had advance
copies of Entangled,--

00:01:04.064 --> 00:01:05.465 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:01:05.465 --> 00:01:06.800 align:middle line:84%
>> -- which was very interesting
'cause it was your first work

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:09.403 align:middle line:84%
of fiction, and you didn't
know how it was going to fly.

00:01:09.403 --> 00:01:10.704 align:middle line:90%
How did it fly?

00:01:10.704 --> 00:01:14.007 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it's been rather
difficult to reinvent myself

00:01:14.007 --> 00:01:16.510 align:middle line:90%
as a novelist in my 60's.

00:01:16.510 --> 00:01:19.813 align:middle line:84%
The publishing industry
likes to keep me in a box

00:01:19.813 --> 00:01:21.948 align:middle line:90%
of writing non-fiction.

00:01:21.948 --> 00:01:27.587 align:middle line:84%
But I feel as a creative
artist that it's my right

00:01:27.587 --> 00:01:29.856 align:middle line:84%
to explore other
areas of my craft.

00:01:29.856 --> 00:01:31.224 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:01:31.224 --> 00:01:35.362 align:middle line:84%
>> And I felt very strongly
called for some time to do some

00:01:35.362 --> 00:01:37.531 align:middle line:84%
of my work in the
realm of fiction.

00:01:37.531 --> 00:01:40.267 align:middle line:90%
But it's very difficult.

00:01:40.267 --> 00:01:43.236 align:middle line:84%
I've had many big
bestsellers in non-fiction.

00:01:43.236 --> 00:01:45.439 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes. You're cash
cow in that genre.

00:01:45.439 --> 00:01:49.108 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes. And now starting
out writing fiction,

00:01:49.108 --> 00:01:51.611 align:middle line:84%
it's like starting again
from the beginning.

00:01:51.611 --> 00:01:53.947 align:middle line:84%
It's like being 25
again, you know.

00:01:53.947 --> 00:01:55.082 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:01:55.082 --> 00:01:57.384 align:middle line:84%
>> And I'm completely
unknown as a novelist

00:01:57.384 --> 00:02:00.620 align:middle line:84%
and the publishing industry
reluctantly publishes my novels

00:02:00.620 --> 00:02:04.825 align:middle line:84%
but doesn't particularly want
to push them or promote them.

00:02:04.825 --> 00:02:08.962 align:middle line:84%
So, it's very-- so Entangled,
those who've read it,

00:02:08.962 --> 00:02:10.764 align:middle line:84%
seem to have visceral
reactions to it.

00:02:10.764 --> 00:02:13.033 align:middle line:84%
People either love it or
hate it, which is fine.

00:02:13.033 --> 00:02:14.534 align:middle line:90%
I'm very happy with either.

00:02:14.534 --> 00:02:16.002 align:middle line:90%
But not a vast majority.

00:02:16.002 --> 00:02:17.471 align:middle line:84%
>> It means they're not
sleeping through it.

00:02:17.471 --> 00:02:19.739 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, not a vast number
of people have read it.

00:02:19.739 --> 00:02:22.943 align:middle line:84%
>> So the interesting thing
we talked about last time was

00:02:22.943 --> 00:02:25.678 align:middle line:84%
that when you are
going non-fiction,

00:02:25.678 --> 00:02:27.614 align:middle line:84%
which you're well-known,
very, very well-known for.

00:02:27.614 --> 00:02:30.417 align:middle line:84%
I mean I started a lot of my
journey based on your work

00:02:30.417 --> 00:02:31.451 align:middle line:90%
about 20 years ago too.

00:02:31.451 --> 00:02:32.719 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:02:32.719 --> 00:02:35.856 align:middle line:84%
>> The problem is you keep
bumping up against science

00:02:35.856 --> 00:02:38.692 align:middle line:84%
and peer review and
all this sort of thing

00:02:38.692 --> 00:02:40.494 align:middle line:84%
and you are pushing
the envelope.

00:02:40.494 --> 00:02:42.662 align:middle line:84%
That's the nature of what
you're-- to do your work.

00:02:42.662 --> 00:02:44.029 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:02:44.029 --> 00:02:46.967 align:middle line:84%
>> So by going into fiction,
aren't you able to kind of jump

00:02:46.967 --> 00:02:49.903 align:middle line:84%
that [inaudible] a bit and
put forth theories that--

00:02:49.903 --> 00:02:52.038 align:middle line:84%
>> Well that's the delight
for me with fiction.

00:02:52.038 --> 00:02:52.739 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:02:52.739 --> 00:02:53.974 align:middle line:90%
>> Because I don't have

00:02:53.974 --> 00:02:56.510 align:middle line:84%
to bulletproof my arguments
with 2,000 footnotes.

00:02:56.510 --> 00:03:02.182 align:middle line:84%
Because to the critics, I can
say, "Relax, it's just fantasy."

00:03:02.182 --> 00:03:06.019 align:middle line:84%
But it becomes possible to
explore extraordinary ideas.

00:03:06.019 --> 00:03:08.555 align:middle line:90%
So in Entangled, I was looking

00:03:08.555 --> 00:03:11.925 align:middle line:84%
at demonic influence
in human affairs.

00:03:11.925 --> 00:03:13.660 align:middle line:90%
I was looking at time travel.

00:03:13.660 --> 00:03:15.896 align:middle line:84%
I was looking at the
role of super na--

00:03:15.896 --> 00:03:19.199 align:middle line:84%
of beneficent supernatural
beings such as the Blue Angel

00:03:19.199 --> 00:03:20.467 align:middle line:90%
who features an Entangled

00:03:20.467 --> 00:03:24.171 align:middle line:84%
that people have been reporting
encounters with entities

00:03:24.171 --> 00:03:25.972 align:middle line:90%
of this type down the ages.

00:03:25.972 --> 00:03:28.175 align:middle line:84%
And science of course
completely dismisses them.

00:03:28.175 --> 00:03:32.178 align:middle line:84%
But I think they've had a huge
role to play in the human story.

00:03:32.178 --> 00:03:34.147 align:middle line:84%
>> And a confluence of
history in a new way

00:03:34.147 --> 00:03:37.751 align:middle line:84%
where you were putting various
considered primitive original

00:03:37.751 --> 00:03:39.786 align:middle line:84%
peoples together in
the same time frame--

00:03:39.786 --> 00:03:40.820 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, yes.

00:03:40.820 --> 00:03:42.055 align:middle line:84%
>> -- interacting
with certain traits.

00:03:42.055 --> 00:03:44.357 align:middle line:84%
>> I mean Entangled involve
one young woman, Leoni,

00:03:44.357 --> 00:03:47.928 align:middle line:84%
in 21st century Los Angeles
and another young woman, Ria,

00:03:47.928 --> 00:03:50.363 align:middle line:84%
24,000 years ago
in the Stone Age.

00:03:50.363 --> 00:03:52.933 align:middle line:84%
And it involved altered
states of consciousness,

00:03:52.933 --> 00:03:54.968 align:middle line:84%
the use of visionary
plants in the case of Ria

00:03:54.968 --> 00:03:58.904 align:middle line:84%
in the Stone Age, psychedelic
mushrooms in the case of Leoni

00:03:58.904 --> 00:04:01.341 align:middle line:84%
in the modern age,
dimethyltryptamine

00:04:01.341 --> 00:04:04.277 align:middle line:84%
and then Ayahuasca in
which the active ingredient

00:04:04.277 --> 00:04:06.446 align:middle line:90%
is dimethyltryptamine.

00:04:06.446 --> 00:04:10.550 align:middle line:84%
And I think perhaps these
are also reasons why the mass

00:04:10.550 --> 00:04:13.186 align:middle line:84%
mainstream audience
didn't go for the book

00:04:13.186 --> 00:04:16.690 align:middle line:84%
because the book is dealing with
very challenging and edgy ideas.

00:04:16.690 --> 00:04:17.924 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:04:17.924 --> 00:04:19.192 align:middle line:84%
>> And it's suggesting that
in these altered states

00:04:19.192 --> 00:04:22.829 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness brought
on by visionary plants,

00:04:22.829 --> 00:04:25.599 align:middle line:84%
we may have incredibly
important experiences

00:04:25.599 --> 00:04:28.435 align:middle line:84%
which might even
make it possible

00:04:28.435 --> 00:04:30.870 align:middle line:84%
to transcend the
barrier of time.

00:04:30.870 --> 00:04:34.574 align:middle line:84%
Once we step out of the body,
once we're no longer confined

00:04:34.574 --> 00:04:38.778 align:middle line:84%
to the material plane, then the
time space continuum no longer

00:04:38.778 --> 00:04:39.980 align:middle line:90%
applies upon us.

00:04:39.980 --> 00:04:42.315 align:middle line:84%
And it might be possible
to visit different epochs,

00:04:42.315 --> 00:04:44.784 align:middle line:84%
perhaps not in physical form,
but in an out of body form.

00:04:44.784 --> 00:04:48.788 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I considered
and explored in Entangled

00:04:48.788 --> 00:04:52.125 align:middle line:84%
because the basic theme
is that with the--

00:04:52.125 --> 00:04:55.295 align:middle line:84%
my two heroines are dealing
with a time traveling demon.

00:04:55.295 --> 00:04:58.031 align:middle line:84%
And that's why the benevolent
force behind the story,--

00:04:58.031 --> 00:04:59.432 align:middle line:90%
>> Very exciting.

00:04:59.432 --> 00:05:03.503 align:middle line:84%
>> -- the Blue Angel needs to
have one person in the timeframe

00:05:03.503 --> 00:05:07.374 align:middle line:84%
of 24,000 years ago and
another one today both working

00:05:07.374 --> 00:05:09.242 align:middle line:84%
to fight this battle
of good against evil.

00:05:09.242 --> 00:05:11.778 align:middle line:84%
>> It was interesting
you chose heroines.

00:05:11.778 --> 00:05:13.079 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:05:13.079 --> 00:05:14.447 align:middle line:84%
>> And then, again, when you
speak about your journeys

00:05:14.447 --> 00:05:16.516 align:middle line:84%
of Ayahuasca, which we'll go
into a minute because I want

00:05:16.516 --> 00:05:18.385 align:middle line:84%
to talk about the
TED Talks controversy

00:05:18.385 --> 00:05:19.920 align:middle line:90%
that is still roaring.

00:05:19.920 --> 00:05:21.154 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:21.154 --> 00:05:22.756 align:middle line:84%
>> Again, it's Mother
Ayahuasca that you connected

00:05:22.756 --> 00:05:23.957 align:middle line:90%
as a feminine essence.

00:05:23.957 --> 00:05:26.059 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, it's a curios
thing I find as a writer.

00:05:26.059 --> 00:05:30.096 align:middle line:84%
I'm not massively attracted
to writing male characters.

00:05:30.096 --> 00:05:33.166 align:middle line:84%
I'm more interested in female
characters and I feel--

00:05:33.166 --> 00:05:34.301 align:middle line:90%
>> Why is that?

00:05:34.301 --> 00:05:35.769 align:middle line:90%
>> I don't know.

00:05:35.769 --> 00:05:40.106 align:middle line:84%
I feel that that much that
is noble and nurturing,

00:05:40.106 --> 00:05:42.508 align:middle line:90%
and courageous, and powerful

00:05:42.508 --> 00:05:46.446 align:middle line:84%
about the human race is
in the feminine side.

00:05:46.446 --> 00:05:51.484 align:middle line:84%
I think we live in a
testosterone-driven epoch today

00:05:51.484 --> 00:05:53.553 align:middle line:90%
and have done for quite a while

00:05:53.553 --> 00:05:57.991 align:middle line:84%
and men have been calling the
shots but with horrific results,

00:05:57.991 --> 00:05:59.492 align:middle line:84%
you know, where there's--
with the--

00:05:59.492 --> 00:06:02.228 align:middle line:84%
the balance of the feminine
i's not been allowed in.

00:06:02.228 --> 00:06:05.432 align:middle line:84%
And we see this culture of
aggression, and competition,

00:06:05.432 --> 00:06:09.302 align:middle line:84%
and warfare, and conspicuous
consumption, and everything

00:06:09.302 --> 00:06:12.072 align:middle line:84%
that goes with that, and I feel
that that comes from a society

00:06:12.072 --> 00:06:14.207 align:middle line:84%
that is overbalanced
in the direction

00:06:14.207 --> 00:06:17.444 align:middle line:84%
of a particularly
narrow interpretation

00:06:17.444 --> 00:06:19.512 align:middle line:90%
of the male energy.

00:06:19.512 --> 00:06:24.250 align:middle line:84%
So I find myself wanting to
honor the feminine in my stories

00:06:24.250 --> 00:06:30.724 align:middle line:84%
and wanting to look at the
massive role, hidden, often,

00:06:30.724 --> 00:06:34.461 align:middle line:84%
but massive in human
affairs that women have had--

00:06:34.461 --> 00:06:35.662 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, and--

00:06:35.662 --> 00:06:37.097 align:middle line:84%
>> -- and the [inaudible]
that they have played.

00:06:37.097 --> 00:06:41.434 align:middle line:84%
>> And for whoever doesn't know,
you chose a very powerful wife,

00:06:41.434 --> 00:06:43.737 align:middle line:84%
a beautiful, powerful
being as your wife,

00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:45.472 align:middle line:84%
so you have this
influence in your life

00:06:45.472 --> 00:06:46.573 align:middle line:90%
with Santha all the time--

00:06:46.573 --> 00:06:47.774 align:middle line:84%
[Inaudible Remark] --
who is your partner.

00:06:47.774 --> 00:06:49.042 align:middle line:84%
And for whoever has read
your book, of course she's

00:06:49.042 --> 00:06:50.844 align:middle line:84%
in beautiful photography
as well.

00:06:50.844 --> 00:06:51.478 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:06:51.478 --> 00:06:52.545 align:middle line:90%
She's my partner--

00:06:52.545 --> 00:06:53.480 align:middle line:84%
>> So you're steeped
in this energy and--

00:06:53.480 --> 00:06:54.447 align:middle line:90%
>> -- and my fellow adventurer.

00:06:54.447 --> 00:06:55.281 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:06:55.281 --> 00:06:58.051 align:middle line:90%
>> And I think I would be lost

00:06:58.051 --> 00:07:00.353 align:middle line:84%
without Santha somewhere
in my life.

00:07:00.353 --> 00:07:01.521 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes. So--

00:07:01.521 --> 00:07:02.389 align:middle line:84%
>> She's been huge
balancing influence for me.

00:07:02.389 --> 00:07:03.723 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:07:03.723 --> 00:07:06.292 align:middle line:84%
Okay, now let's talk about
the journeys, the Ayahuasca--

00:07:06.292 --> 00:07:08.361 align:middle line:90%
Mother Ayahuasca and so forth.

00:07:08.361 --> 00:07:09.462 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:07:09.462 --> 00:07:11.765 align:middle line:84%
>> And before we go
into the details of more

00:07:11.765 --> 00:07:13.566 align:middle line:84%
or less your visions
and discoveries,

00:07:13.566 --> 00:07:15.802 align:middle line:84%
let's talk about the fact--
you talked about it publicly

00:07:15.802 --> 00:07:17.704 align:middle line:90%
at the TED Talks event.

00:07:17.704 --> 00:07:18.772 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, I did.

00:07:18.772 --> 00:07:21.574 align:middle line:84%
>> And you talked
about your background,

00:07:21.574 --> 00:07:24.544 align:middle line:84%
where you had been doing a
lot of cannabis in the past

00:07:24.544 --> 00:07:27.447 align:middle line:84%
and your journey through that
and out the other side of that,

00:07:27.447 --> 00:07:28.515 align:middle line:90%
what had happened with you.

00:07:28.515 --> 00:07:31.418 align:middle line:84%
It was a very personal
and powerful talk.

00:07:31.418 --> 00:07:36.055 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, I told the personal
story and I felt naively

00:07:36.055 --> 00:07:38.425 align:middle line:84%
that TED was the right
place to tell that story.

00:07:38.425 --> 00:07:39.626 align:middle line:90%
>> You were invited, right?

00:07:39.626 --> 00:07:42.061 align:middle line:84%
>> I was invited and I was
invited to a conference

00:07:42.061 --> 00:07:43.430 align:middle line:84%
of which the theme
was, you know,

00:07:43.430 --> 00:07:45.498 align:middle line:84%
"Challenging Existing
Paradigms",

00:07:45.498 --> 00:07:46.800 align:middle line:90%
so I felt write at home--

00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:47.467 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:07:47.467 --> 00:07:49.903 align:middle line:90%
>> -- in that theme.

00:07:49.903 --> 00:07:54.941 align:middle line:84%
And I was also aware that people
in previous TED Talks had talked

00:07:54.941 --> 00:07:56.508 align:middle line:84%
about psychedelics,
so I didn't see why

00:07:56.508 --> 00:08:00.180 align:middle line:90%
that should be a problem either.

00:08:00.180 --> 00:08:05.318 align:middle line:84%
And the personal element
of my story which I relayed

00:08:05.318 --> 00:08:08.688 align:middle line:84%
in that talk is very-- is really
very straightforward which is

00:08:08.688 --> 00:08:10.356 align:middle line:90%
that Ayahuasca is known

00:08:10.356 --> 00:08:13.259 align:middle line:84%
as a healing agency
amongst other things,

00:08:13.259 --> 00:08:16.596 align:middle line:84%
this entity that people all
around the world encounter

00:08:16.596 --> 00:08:18.331 align:middle line:84%
in the Ayahuasca
experience and tend

00:08:18.331 --> 00:08:20.099 align:middle line:90%
to construe as Mother Ayahuasca.

00:08:20.099 --> 00:08:24.337 align:middle line:84%
And I was very careful to say
in the TED Talk, I make no claim

00:08:24.337 --> 00:08:26.339 align:middle line:84%
to the reality status
of this entity.

00:08:26.339 --> 00:08:29.876 align:middle line:84%
I'm simply reporting the
phenomenology that people all

00:08:29.876 --> 00:08:31.511 align:middle line:90%
over the world are encountering

00:08:31.511 --> 00:08:34.914 align:middle line:84%
in intelligence what they
interpret as in intelligence

00:08:34.914 --> 00:08:36.014 align:middle line:90%
when they drink Ayahuasca.

00:08:36.014 --> 00:08:38.951 align:middle line:84%
And most often, she
appears in female form.

00:08:38.951 --> 00:08:42.155 align:middle line:84%
Although she's a shapeshifter,
she may sometimes come

00:08:42.155 --> 00:08:46.192 align:middle line:84%
as a jaguar, sometimes
as a serpent,

00:08:46.192 --> 00:08:48.528 align:middle line:90%
sometimes as a human woman.

00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:52.365 align:middle line:84%
And she has powerful lessons
to teach us about ourselves.

00:08:52.365 --> 00:08:56.035 align:middle line:84%
So, although you sense a power
of love in this intelligence

00:08:56.035 --> 00:08:59.672 align:middle line:84%
that you encounter, it's
a kind of tough love.

00:08:59.672 --> 00:09:01.074 align:middle line:90%
You know, she--

00:09:01.074 --> 00:09:02.909 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you have reality reflected
back at you at something?

00:09:02.909 --> 00:09:05.678 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah. She will not let
you off the hook lightly.

00:09:05.678 --> 00:09:08.548 align:middle line:84%
You are confronted with the
truth about your own behavior.

00:09:08.548 --> 00:09:12.151 align:middle line:84%
And something that was bending
my behavior out of shape

00:09:12.151 --> 00:09:19.025 align:middle line:84%
for many, many years was my
own personal abuse of cannabis.

00:09:19.025 --> 00:09:22.529 align:middle line:84%
When I talk about cannabis, I
want to make it absolutely clear

00:09:22.529 --> 00:09:26.032 align:middle line:84%
that I have nothing against
cannabis, and I celebrate

00:09:26.032 --> 00:09:29.402 align:middle line:84%
and honor the right of
adults, the sovereign right

00:09:29.402 --> 00:09:31.170 align:middle line:84%
to make choices over
their own bodies

00:09:31.170 --> 00:09:34.674 align:middle line:84%
