is what gets you high.

00:16:40.333 --> 00:16:44.136 align:middle line:84%
And the other is CBD, okay,
which doesn't get you high.

00:16:44.136 --> 00:16:49.175 align:middle line:84%
And at the level of the
studies that have been done,

00:16:49.175 --> 00:16:55.247 align:middle line:84%
it seems that there is some
risk of THC-inducing psychosis.

00:16:55.247 --> 00:16:56.349 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:16:56.349 --> 00:17:01.420 align:middle line:84%
>> The CBD is a powerful
antipsychotic agent.

00:17:01.420 --> 00:17:05.224 align:middle line:84%
And in the natural herb, these
two ingredients balanced.

00:17:05.224 --> 00:17:07.726 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes. So you giggle
and eat too much.

00:17:07.726 --> 00:17:08.394 align:middle line:90%
>> So it gets you high--

00:17:08.394 --> 00:17:09.428 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:17:09.428 --> 00:17:10.329 align:middle line:84%
>> -- but it doesn't
make you paranoid.

00:17:10.329 --> 00:17:11.429 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:17:11.429 --> 00:17:15.701 align:middle line:84%
>> Okay? But the very
engineered varieties

00:17:15.701 --> 00:17:19.638 align:middle line:84%
that we are now dealing with
have almost entirely got rid

00:17:19.638 --> 00:17:23.309 align:middle line:84%
of the CBD and they're
almost 100 percent THC.

00:17:23.309 --> 00:17:24.409 align:middle line:90%
>> Okay.

00:17:24.409 --> 00:17:26.078 align:middle line:84%
>> And that I think is
part of the problem.

00:17:26.078 --> 00:17:30.316 align:middle line:84%
And if we lived in a rational
society which was not governed

00:17:30.316 --> 00:17:34.286 align:middle line:84%
by the truly insane and
grotesque war on drugs,

00:17:34.286 --> 00:17:36.255 align:middle line:84%
then it would-- we
would have this problem.

00:17:36.255 --> 00:17:39.458 align:middle line:84%
The reason we have this
problem is that, you know,

00:17:39.458 --> 00:17:43.129 align:middle line:84%
growers are looking for
the maximum amount of high

00:17:43.129 --> 00:17:45.998 align:middle line:84%
that they can concentrate
into a bud.

00:17:45.998 --> 00:17:48.434 align:middle line:84%
Whereas, you know, what we
really should be looking

00:17:48.434 --> 00:17:50.436 align:middle line:90%
for is a balanced experience

00:17:50.436 --> 00:17:53.572 align:middle line:84%
which is what the
traditional herb offers.

00:17:53.572 --> 00:17:55.741 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, somebody
like me, I might be--

00:17:55.741 --> 00:17:58.778 align:middle line:84%
if I live in a society where
I could make sovereign choices

00:17:58.778 --> 00:18:02.248 align:middle line:84%
over my own consciousness and
I wanted to smoke cannabis,

00:18:02.248 --> 00:18:04.316 align:middle line:84%
I could go to a grower
and say, "Well, you know,

00:18:04.316 --> 00:18:07.586 align:middle line:84%
fix me a strain that's very high
in CBD and very low in THC."

00:18:07.586 --> 00:18:09.255 align:middle line:90%
And that might be-- you know,

00:18:09.255 --> 00:18:10.756 align:middle line:84%
I might have a complete
different experience

00:18:10.756 --> 00:18:11.390 align:middle line:90%
with that too.

00:18:11.390 --> 00:18:12.792 align:middle line:90%
Who knows?

00:18:12.792 --> 00:18:14.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Well I'm wondering, this is
where my mind is going with it

00:18:14.360 --> 00:18:17.897 align:middle line:84%
which is, okay, now
you have the THC

00:18:17.897 --> 00:18:20.933 align:middle line:84%
and you have a possible
propensity

00:18:20.933 --> 00:18:23.836 align:middle line:90%
for producing psychotic states.

00:18:23.836 --> 00:18:26.605 align:middle line:84%
When you look at psychotic
states and you look at the entry

00:18:26.605 --> 00:18:30.176 align:middle line:84%
of paranoia and influences,
is it possible

00:18:30.176 --> 00:18:32.078 align:middle line:84%
that you're then
also interfacing

00:18:32.078 --> 00:18:35.414 align:middle line:84%
with other dimensional
fields or other realities

00:18:35.414 --> 00:18:39.885 align:middle line:84%
that are also may
be boosting some

00:18:39.885 --> 00:18:42.688 align:middle line:84%
of those effects
within the psyche?

00:18:42.688 --> 00:18:44.757 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, I think that my work

00:18:44.757 --> 00:18:49.595 align:middle line:84%
over the last few years has
opened me up to this possibility

00:18:49.595 --> 00:18:54.900 align:middle line:84%
which is that the brain is not a
generator of consciousness but,

00:18:54.900 --> 00:18:58.904 align:middle line:84%
in a sense, a transceiver
of consciousness.

00:18:58.904 --> 00:19:00.172 align:middle line:90%
And if that is the case,

00:19:00.172 --> 00:19:04.176 align:middle line:84%
then when you alter the receiver
wavelength of the brain,

00:19:04.176 --> 00:19:06.846 align:middle line:84%
other realms of consciousness
that are normally closed off

00:19:06.846 --> 00:19:08.614 align:middle line:84%
to our sense may
become accessible.

00:19:08.614 --> 00:19:12.952 align:middle line:84%
And I think that is one
of the primary functions

00:19:12.952 --> 00:19:14.720 align:middle line:90%
of the powerful psychedelics.

00:19:14.720 --> 00:19:18.524 align:middle line:84%
And that, I believe, is what
is going on with Ayahuasca.

00:19:18.524 --> 00:19:21.594 align:middle line:84%
And I think this is one of the
things that really annoyed TED

00:19:21.594 --> 00:19:24.563 align:middle line:84%
about my talk in the sense
that I was suggesting

00:19:24.563 --> 00:19:27.733 align:middle line:84%
that I never claimed
that this is a fact,

00:19:27.733 --> 00:19:30.770 align:middle line:84%
I just said that it's a
possibility, that let's consider

00:19:30.770 --> 00:19:32.505 align:middle line:84%
that we are dealing
with some kind

00:19:32.505 --> 00:19:36.609 align:middle line:84%
of non-physical intelligence
or non-physical entity

00:19:36.609 --> 00:19:39.712 align:middle line:84%
which has the best interest
of the human race at heart

00:19:39.712 --> 00:19:43.482 align:middle line:84%
and which is using the Ayahuasca
state to communicate with us.

00:19:43.482 --> 00:19:46.218 align:middle line:84%
And that was perhaps
why I got my healing

00:19:46.218 --> 00:19:47.720 align:middle line:90%
because I encountered an entity

00:19:47.720 --> 00:19:49.822 align:middle line:84%
that did not have the best
interest of the human race

00:19:49.822 --> 00:19:53.626 align:middle line:84%
at heart, would not bring about
miraculous healing experiences

00:19:53.626 --> 00:19:55.194 align:middle line:90%
and I'm not the sole case.

00:19:55.194 --> 00:19:56.929 align:middle line:84%
There are pe-- people
have gotten into admission

00:19:56.929 --> 00:20:00.766 align:middle line:84%
of severe terminal cancers
following Ayahuasca experiences.

00:20:00.766 --> 00:20:03.169 align:middle line:84%
Again, I make no
claims about this.

00:20:03.169 --> 00:20:04.370 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:20:04.370 --> 00:20:05.571 align:middle line:84%
>> But there are many,
many cases on the record.

00:20:05.571 --> 00:20:07.439 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, they've also
kicked other heavy drugs.

00:20:07.439 --> 00:20:10.442 align:middle line:84%
>> And huge addictions
to cocaine

00:20:10.442 --> 00:20:14.213 align:middle line:84%
and heroin have been
healed as a result

00:20:14.213 --> 00:20:16.048 align:middle line:90%
of in counsel with Ayahuasca.

00:20:16.048 --> 00:20:20.252 align:middle line:84%
So-- and there's the sense of
this loving intelligent entity

00:20:20.252 --> 00:20:22.087 align:middle line:90%
that lies beyond the veil

00:20:22.087 --> 00:20:27.826 align:middle line:84%
who in some ways using the
Ayahuasca brew to gain contact

00:20:27.826 --> 00:20:29.228 align:middle line:84%
with us at the level
of consciousness.

00:20:29.228 --> 00:20:31.263 align:middle line:90%
But, here's the thing.

00:20:31.263 --> 00:20:33.699 align:middle line:84%
It's important I
think to recognize,

00:20:33.699 --> 00:20:37.870 align:middle line:84%
and experiences I've had have
manifested this to me also,

00:20:37.870 --> 00:20:40.840 align:middle line:84%
that just as in this world,
in this physical realm,

00:20:40.840 --> 00:20:42.308 align:middle line:90%
there is good and evil.

00:20:42.308 --> 00:20:46.912 align:middle line:84%
So, also in other levels of
reality, there is good and evil.

00:20:46.912 --> 00:20:48.380 align:middle line:84%
>> There are opportunistic
beings.

00:20:48.380 --> 00:20:49.748 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:20:49.748 --> 00:20:52.551 align:middle line:84%
>> There are opportunistic,
parasitical, vampirish entities

00:20:52.551 --> 00:20:56.455 align:middle line:84%
out there who feed on pain
and misery and suffering.

00:20:56.455 --> 00:21:00.759 align:middle line:84%
And that's the danger when you
enter a deeply altered state

00:21:00.759 --> 00:21:02.061 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness.

00:21:02.061 --> 00:21:04.797 align:middle line:84%
And that's why the role of
the shaman is so important,

00:21:04.797 --> 00:21:10.035 align:middle line:84%
is that once you open that door
and go through into that realm,

00:21:10.035 --> 00:21:13.105 align:middle line:84%
Mother Ayahuasca is not
the only entity out there

00:21:13.105 --> 00:21:15.040 align:middle line:90%
and there are other entities

00:21:15.040 --> 00:21:19.111 align:middle line:84%
which have a propounding
negative agenda for humanity,

00:21:19.111 --> 00:21:24.450 align:middle line:84%
and which are likely influencing
humanity even when we're not

00:21:24.450 --> 00:21:26.418 align:middle line:84%
in altered states of
consciousness, perhaps entered

00:21:26.418 --> 00:21:28.420 align:middle line:84%
through dreams, perhaps
in another ways.

00:21:28.420 --> 00:21:29.255 align:middle line:90%
>> Through fatigue.

00:21:29.255 --> 00:21:30.356 align:middle line:90%
>> Through fatigue.

00:21:30.356 --> 00:21:32.558 align:middle line:84%
That there is this--
this is connection.

00:21:32.558 --> 00:21:34.994 align:middle line:84%
And this is why shamanism
is very interesting

00:21:34.994 --> 00:21:38.931 align:middle line:84%
because shamanism says, "Look,
whether you like it or not,

00:21:38.931 --> 00:21:41.333 align:middle line:84%
we are immersed in
unseen realms."

00:21:41.333 --> 00:21:42.534 align:middle line:90%
They're around us all the time.

00:21:42.534 --> 00:21:43.869 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:21:43.869 --> 00:21:45.504 align:middle line:84%
>> And we better be proactive
in how we deal with them.

00:21:45.504 --> 00:21:46.906 align:middle line:90%
That's what a shaman is.

00:21:46.906 --> 00:21:50.242 align:middle line:84%
A shaman is the person who has
trained and learned the system

00:21:50.242 --> 00:21:53.345 align:middle line:84%
to go over there and
master spirits and to deal

00:21:53.345 --> 00:21:55.214 align:middle line:84%
with who is not to
be their victim.

00:21:55.214 --> 00:21:57.249 align:middle line:84%
And may be-- you know,
may be that's what--

00:21:57.249 --> 00:22:01.453 align:middle line:84%
that's what the poor
suffering schizophrenic is--

00:22:01.453 --> 00:22:03.188 align:middle line:90%
>> I've often thought that, yes.

00:22:03.188 --> 00:22:04.823 align:middle line:90%
>> -- is the person who--

00:22:04.823 --> 00:22:07.960 align:middle line:84%
is the person who is
open to the other realms

00:22:07.960 --> 00:22:09.962 align:middle line:84%
but does not have the
training or the system

00:22:09.962 --> 00:22:11.297 align:middle line:90%
of control that a shaman has.

00:22:11.297 --> 00:22:12.064 align:middle line:90%
>> No filters.

00:22:12.064 --> 00:22:13.332 align:middle line:90%
>> No filters, whatsoever,

00:22:13.332 --> 00:22:17.102 align:middle line:84%
and cannot manage the
experiences that come through.

00:22:17.102 --> 00:22:19.471 align:middle line:84%
So, shamans are very
useful individuals.

00:22:19.471 --> 00:22:21.540 align:middle line:84%
They have trained
often from an early age

00:22:21.540 --> 00:22:24.777 align:middle line:84%
and they have special aptitudes
and abilities in this world not

00:22:24.777 --> 00:22:28.247 align:middle line:84%
to be dominated by spirits
but to master that realm

00:22:28.247 --> 00:22:30.382 align:middle line:84%
and to operate with
confidence and security.

00:22:30.382 --> 00:22:31.717 align:middle line:84%
And so, that when
they enter that realm,

00:22:31.717 --> 00:22:33.185 align:middle line:90%
they're not disoriented.

00:22:33.185 --> 00:22:34.887 align:middle line:90%
They're not in a state of fear.

00:22:34.887 --> 00:22:37.456 align:middle line:84%
They know what they're doing,
and they can manage it.

00:22:37.456 --> 00:22:40.225 align:middle line:84%
So, all of these
to say, and again,

00:22:40.225 --> 00:22:42.728 align:middle line:84%
I claim no factual
basis for this.

00:22:42.728 --> 00:22:43.162 align:middle line:90%
I've done no--

00:22:43.162 --> 00:22:43.996 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:22:43.996 --> 00:22:44.697 align:middle line:90%
>> -- experiments to prove this.

00:22:44.697 --> 00:22:46.131 align:middle line:90%
I'm simply expressing

00:22:46.131 --> 00:22:49.401 align:middle line:84%
to you what I think may be the
case based on some experiences,

00:22:49.401 --> 00:22:51.103 align:middle line:84%
quite a number of
experiences that I've had

00:22:51.103 --> 00:22:54.473 align:middle line:84%
that there are dark and
negative forces out there,

00:22:54.473 --> 00:22:58.210 align:middle line:84%
as well as brilliant
forces of light and love.

00:22:58.210 --> 00:23:01.313 align:middle line:84%
And-- that in a sense,
our predicament

00:23:01.313 --> 00:23:02.815 align:middle line:84%
of human beings whether
we're dealing

00:23:02.815 --> 00:23:05.184 align:middle line:84%
in the realm beyond the veil
or whether we're dealing

00:23:05.184 --> 00:23:08.654 align:middle line:84%
in this material realm is always
the predicament to choose.

00:23:08.654 --> 00:23:11.490 align:middle line:84%
We have those choices
between good and evil,

00:23:11.490 --> 00:23:13.359 align:middle line:90%
between dark and light.

00:23:13.359 --> 00:23:16.995 align:middle line:84%
And many people have said
to me, "Oh, you know,

00:23:16.995 --> 00:23:18.464 align:middle line:90%
all is one, all is unity.

00:23:18.464 --> 00:23:20.632 align:middle line:84%
All is beautiful in the
world," this is one reason why,

00:23:20.632 --> 00:23:23.068 align:middle line:90%
by a lot of people, those

00:23:23.068 --> 00:23:25.471 align:middle line:84%
who dislike my novel
Entangled disliked it

00:23:25.471 --> 00:23:28.841 align:middle line:84%
because I showed forces of
darkness and forces of evil

00:23:28.841 --> 00:23:32.444 align:middle line:84%
at work and how they can impact
and influence human beings.

00:23:32.444 --> 00:23:34.046 align:middle line:84%
And that probably we're
not supposed to believe

00:23:34.046 --> 00:23:37.516 align:middle line:84%
in such things because if
we even for a moment suggest

00:23:37.516 --> 00:23:41.453 align:middle line:84%
that such things exist, then it
will make things worse rather

00:23:41.453 --> 00:23:42.488 align:middle line:90%
than better.

00:23:42.488 --> 00:23:46.091 align:middle line:84%
But I believe that
actually we do have

00:23:46.091 --> 00:23:47.526 align:middle line:90%
to get to grips with this.

00:23:47.526 --> 00:23:49.661 align:middle line:84%
We cannot stick our
heads in the sand--

00:23:49.661 --> 00:23:50.996 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely not.

00:23:50.996 --> 00:23:53.298 align:middle line:84%
>> -- and pretend that there
is no wickedness and no evil

00:23:53.298 --> 00:23:55.701 align:middle line:84%
and that all is good and
that all is rosy and perfect

00:23:55.701 --> 00:23:59.204 align:middle line:90%
in the garden, because it's not.

00:23:59.204 --> 00:24:03.842 align:middle line:84%
And in a way, the
horrible character

00:24:03.842 --> 00:24:08.180 align:middle line:84%
in Entangled who's called
Sulpa, who's a demon,

00:24:08.180 --> 00:24:11.850 align:middle line:84%
who is impacting human behavior,
he's like a sort of Hitler

00:24:11.850 --> 00:24:13.252 align:middle line:90%
of the Stone Age, you know.

00:24:13.252 --> 00:24:15.587 align:middle line:84%
And Hitler could
not have been dealt

00:24:15.587 --> 00:24:18.023 align:middle line:84%
with by everybody sticking
their heads in the sand.

00:24:18.023 --> 00:24:20.592 align:middle line:84%
At a certain point,
evil is so bad.

00:24:20.592 --> 00:24:21.527 align:middle line:90%
You have to fight it.

00:24:21.527 --> 00:24:23.095 align:middle line:90%
You have to take a stand.

00:24:23.095 --> 00:24:25.531 align:middle line:84%
You can't just ignore
it and wish it away

00:24:25.531 --> 00:24:27.199 align:middle line:90%
and cover it in rosy light.

00:24:27.199 --> 00:24:30.335 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, and even the most
respected ancient hollowed

00:24:30.335 --> 00:24:34.173 align:middle line:84%
into text all acknowledge
that you have the light

00:24:34.173 --> 00:24:35.007 align:middle line:90%
and you have the darkness.

00:24:35.007 --> 00:24:35.941 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:24:35.941 --> 00:24:37.142 align:middle line:84%
>> You have forces
on both sides.

00:24:37.142 --> 00:24:39.511 align:middle line:84%
You have opportunities for
learning between the two

00:24:39.511 --> 00:24:40.712 align:middle line:90%
and bouncing off of it.

00:24:40.712 --> 00:24:44.249 align:middle line:84%
>> And what would we have
to learn in this plane

00:24:44.249 --> 00:24:48.187 align:middle line:84%
if we were not obliged to make
choices between good and evil?

00:24:48.187 --> 00:24:50.522 align:middle line:84%
If-- what would we--
what would, in a sense,

00:24:50.522 --> 00:24:53.158 align:middle line:84%
what would be the point
of the human experience

00:24:53.158 --> 00:24:54.960 align:middle line:90%
if there was no challenge in it?

00:24:54.960 --> 00:24:58.397 align:middle line:84%
If there was-- if there was no
point at which we were tested

00:24:58.397 --> 00:25:00.599 align:middle line:90%
to make one choice or another?

00:25:00.599 --> 00:25:03.001 align:middle line:84%
If everything was just set
out and prepared for us

00:25:03.001 --> 00:25:06.205 align:middle line:84%
from the beginning by a
divine and beautiful universe

00:25:06.205 --> 00:25:08.874 align:middle line:84%
and all we had to do was
just live unexamined lives

00:25:08.874 --> 00:25:11.343 align:middle line:84%
and just get a-- I don't
see the point of that.

00:25:11.343 --> 00:25:14.813 align:middle line:84%
I think the great thing
about this incredible garden

00:25:14.813 --> 00:25:17.783 align:middle line:84%
that we call planet Earth and
the incredible opportunity

00:25:17.783 --> 00:25:20.819 align:middle line:84%
of being born in a human
body is that day by day,

00:25:20.819 --> 00:25:23.388 align:middle line:84%
minute by minute,
actually, second by second,

00:25:23.388 --> 00:25:25.157 align:middle line:90%
we are required to make choices.

00:25:25.157 --> 00:25:25.991 align:middle line:90%
>> Choices, yes.

00:25:25.991 --> 00:25:27.926 align:middle line:90%
>> And those choices define us,

00:25:27.926 --> 00:25:30.963 align:middle line:84%
and we sometimes make
the wrong choices.

00:25:30.963 --> 00:25:33.899 align:middle line:84%
And the great thing about
having a long human life is the

00:25:33.899 --> 00:25:36.635 align:middle line:84%
opportunity to realize that
you've made the wrong choices

00:25:36.635 --> 00:25:39.438 align:middle line:84%
and the opportunity to learn
from the mistakes you've made

00:25:39.438 --> 00:25:43.475 align:middle line:84%
and to correct your behavior so
that at the end, you may come

00:25:43.475 --> 00:25:46.778 align:middle line:84%
to that Judgment Hall of
Osiris or the Hall of Maat

00:25:46.778 --> 00:25:52.084 align:middle line:84%
as the ancient Egyptians called
it, and you may look back

00:25:52.084 --> 00:25:55.053 align:middle line:84%
on the course of your own life
rather as though it were a work

00:25:55.053 --> 00:25:58.090 align:middle line:84%
of sculpture that you had been
working on for many years.

00:25:58.090 --> 00:26:01.193 align:middle line:84%
And here you made a mistake
and here it was a blemish.

00:26:01.193 --> 00:26:03.295 align:middle line:84%
But as you continued,
you improved

00:26:03.295 --> 00:26:04.429 align:middle line:90%
and perfected your work.

00:26:04.429 --> 00:26:07.533 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of it,
what you should be able

00:26:07.533 --> 00:26:11.303 align:middle line:84%
to do is look back and say,
"Through it all, I did good."

00:26:11.303 --> 00:26:13.138 align:middle line:84%
>> That's a beautiful
way of putting it.

00:26:13.138 --> 00:26:16.041 align:middle line:84%
It leaves people with a very
beautiful vision of that.

00:26:16.041 --> 00:26:16.875 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:26:16.875 --> 00:26:18.176 align:middle line:90%
>> And if you look at it, to me,

00:26:18.176 --> 00:26:21.680 align:middle line:84%
it seems that the higher
one's tolerance for pain,

00:26:21.680 --> 00:26:24.683 align:middle line:84%
the longer it takes on that
path toward making this

00:26:24.683 --> 00:26:25.717 align:middle line:90%
beautiful sculpture.

00:26:25.717 --> 00:26:27.085 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:26:27.085 --> 00:26:29.755 align:middle line:84%
>> And everyone is on their
own path in terms of the amount

00:26:29.755 --> 00:26:31.557 align:middle line:84%
of pain you can handle
before you have

00:26:31.557 --> 00:26:32.824 align:middle line:90%
to make a course correction.

00:26:32.824 --> 00:26:33.659 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:26:33.659 --> 00:26:34.426 align:middle line:90%
>> And that we're all doing it.

00:26:34.426 --> 00:26:35.561 align:middle line:90%
>> And we're all doing it.

00:26:35.561 --> 00:26:36.728 align:middle line:84%
>> We're all doing it at
different stages and--

00:26:36.728 --> 00:26:37.496 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:26:37.496 --> 00:26:38.630 align:middle line:90%
>> -- different lifetimes.

00:26:38.630 --> 00:26:39.665 align:middle line:84%
>> And that's what makes
me think that we are--

00:26:39.665 --> 00:26:41.033 align:middle line:84%
that that's what
we're here to do.

00:26:41.033 --> 00:26:42.267 align:middle line:90%
We're here to learn.

00:26:42.267 --> 00:26:45.938 align:middle line:84%
There's an opportunity
here, incredible opportunity

00:26:45.938 --> 00:26:48.640 align:middle line:84%
for the gradual perfection
of the soul.

00:26:48.640 --> 00:26:50.008 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:26:50.008 --> 00:26:51.643 align:middle line:84%
>> That's where-- that's why
did many lifetimes which I also

00:26:51.643 --> 00:26:53.412 align:middle line:84%
so happen to believe in
and then can approve.

00:26:53.412 --> 00:26:54.212 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, so do I.

00:26:54.212 --> 00:26:55.214 align:middle line:90%
I agree with you.

00:26:55.214 --> 00:26:57.082 align:middle line:84%
Okay, so when we're
looking at this,

00:26:57.082 --> 00:27:01.053 align:middle line:84%
going back just a moment ago, we
were talking about the ability

00:27:01.053 --> 00:27:04.122 align:middle line:84%
of Mother Ayahuasca
to connect with people

00:27:04.122 --> 00:27:05.257 align:middle line:90%
who have addiction issues.

